    <dc:identifier>SIO_010064</dc:identifier>
    <dcterms:description xml:lang="en">The five prime untranslated region (5' UTR) is a section of messenger RNA (mRNA) and the DNA that codes for it that starts at the +1 position (where transcription begins) and ends one nucleotide before the start codon (usually AUG) of the coding region.</dcterms:description>
