    <dcterms:alternative xml:lang="en">coding sequence</dcterms:alternative>
    <dc:description xml:lang="en">A protein coding sequence (CDS) is the region of DNA that is translated to form proteins. The CDS refers to those nucleotides (concatenated exons) that can be divided into codons which are actually translated into amino acids by the ribosomal translation machinery.</dc:description>
