  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://semanticscience.org/resource/SignLanguage">
    <dcterms:description xml:lang="en">A sign language (also signed language) is a language that involves manual communication and body language to convey meaning. This can involve simultaneously combining hand shapes, orientation and movement of the hands, arms or body, and facial expressions to fluidly express a speaker's thoughts.</dcterms:description>
